cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

This paper is about a tool for analyzing and comparing iterative optimization heuristics, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The tool also involves statistical evaluation and tracking of algorithm parameters, which are related to data analysis and machine learning, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as additional likely sub-categories. Finally, the tool can be used for the design of (self-)adaptive algorithms, which is related to control and optimization, indicating cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category.
